codex
The failure is exact and reproducible at browser launch, before the test body runs: Playwright expects Chromium revision `1148`, but that executable is absent. My ranked hypotheses are: (1) the installed Playwright package and available browser cache are revision-mismatched; (2) the prior run unintentionally changed the lockfile/package resolution; (3) the host has a usable Chrome/Chromium binary but Playwright is not configured to select it. I’ll test those in that order; the E2E assertions themselves are not yet implicated.
